Portuguese Stocks: Banco Comercial, Espirito Santo, Galp, SAG

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-03-14T17:17:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/portuguese-stocks-banco-comercial-espirito-santo-are-active.html
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  rose 69.35,
or 0.9 percent, to 7,965.37 at the 4:30 p.m. close in Lisbon,
the first gain in four days.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Portuguese market today.    Banco Espirito Santo SA (BES)  , Portugal’s biggest
publicly traded bank, advanced 2.8 percent to 3.25 euros.
European leaders early on March 12, and two weeks sooner than
investors expected, agreed to broaden the size and scope of
their 440 billion-euro ($614 billion) bailout fund and ease the
terms of Greek rescue loans. Yields on Portuguese 10-year and 5-
year government bonds declined today.    Banco Comercial Portugues SA (BCP)  , Portugal’s second-
biggest publicly traded bank by market value, climbed 3.5
percent to 65.4 euro cents.  Banco BPI SA (BPI)   rose 0.9
percent to 1.39 euros.    Galp Energia SGPS SA (GALP)   advanced 0.6 percent to
15.35 euros. Portugal’s biggest oil company aims to raise about
2 billion euros from a capital increase at its Brazilian unit as
it develops offshore projects in the Latin American nation.    SAG Gest-Solucoes Automovel Globais SGPS SA (SVA)  , a
Portuguese distributor of Volkswagen AG cars, dropped 4.2
percent to 46 cents. The Portuguese government wants to increase
a tax charged on cars as part of its additional measures to cut
the country’s budget deficit, Diario Economico reported, citing
Sergio Vasques, secretary of state for fiscal affairs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joao Lima in Lisbon at 
